# Phase 2: Advanced SEO Strategy & Pending Optimizations

To achieve dominant search engine visibility across all targeted Indian cities (Bengaluru, Chennai, Pune, etc.) and global platforms (US, EMEA, Australia), we must move beyond baseline technical SEO. 

Drawing from 15 years of enterprise B2B SEO experience, here is my end-to-end evaluation of what separates a "good" site from an **industry-leading** site, and exactly what is still pending.

---

## 1. Local & Global Dominance (Programmatic SEO & i18n)
Currently, your location targeting is limited to keyword stuffing in the `services.js` file (e.g., mentioning "Pune" in the metadata). Google's algorithm strongly prefers dedicated, highly relevant pages for local queries.

*   **Pending: Programmatic City Pages**: We need to dynamically generate location-specific landing pages. For example: `/services/engineering/product-design/pune` vs `/services/engineering/product-design/bengaluru`. This allows us to inject local schema, local case studies, and exact-match H1 tags.
*   **Pending: Internationalization (Hreflang)**: To rank natively in the US, EMEA, and Australia without triggering duplicate content penalties, we need Next.js i18n routing (`/en-us/`, `/en-in/`) and `<link rel="alternate" hreflang="x" />` tags in the document head.

## 2. Core Web Vitals (Advanced Performance)
While we fixed the Largest Contentful Paint (LCP) by adding `next/image`, we are currently failing on **Cumulative Layout Shift (CLS)** and **First Contentful Paint (FCP)** due to font loading.

*   **Pending: Next.js Font Optimization**: In `globals.css`, you are using `@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com...')` to load the Inter font. This causes a render-blocking request and FOIT (Flash of Invisible Text). We must refactor the app to use `next/font/google`. This self-hosts the font at build time, resulting in zero layout shift and instant text rendering.

## 3. Advanced Schema Markup (JSON-LD)
We added Organization and Service schema, but we are leaving highly-visible "Rich Snippets" on the table.

*   **Pending: FAQPage Schema**: You have beautifully designed FAQ sections on the Homepage and Contact page. By wrapping these in `FAQPage` JSON-LD schema, Google will often display your Q&As directly on the search results page, pushing competitors down and increasing your click-through rate (CTR).
*   **Pending: BreadcrumbList Schema**: Injecting breadcrumb schema tells Google exactly how your site architecture works, allowing them to display clean navigation paths in the search results instead of messy URLs.

## 4. Dynamic Open Graph Generation (Social SEO)
Currently, if someone shares 10 different service pages on LinkedIn, they will all look exactly the same because we rely on a static fallback image.

*   **Pending: `@vercel/og` Image Generation**: We need to implement dynamic edge-rendered Open Graph images. When a URL is shared, Next.js should programmatically generate a beautiful branded image card that includes the specific Service Title (e.g., "Industrial Automation Services") and the EMEA logo. This drastically increases social CTR.

## 5. Pillar-Cluster Content Architecture
B2B engineering is a high-trust, high-ticket industry. Ranking for "Engineering Services Bengaluru" is hard. Ranking for "How CFD Simulation Reduces Thermal Stress in Oil Pipelines" is much easier and highly converting.

*   **Pending: Insights / Knowledge Hub**: We need to establish a `/insights` or `/case-studies` route. This allows us to target long-tail keywords. We then internally link these specific articles back to your core "money" pages (e.g., the Product Design service page). This builds massive Topical Authority.

---

### Summary of the Next Execution Sprint
If we want to build the ultimate SEO foundation, these are the immediate technical steps I would take next:
1. Replace `@import` fonts with `next/font/google`.
2. Implement `FAQPage` schema on the Contact page.
3. Architect the Next.js Dynamic Routes for City-Specific landing pages.
